Ke Huy Quan & Hong Chau would be deported from the UK under  government plans.  It's astounding to me that my Vietnamese neighbours as a child, who had arrived by boat, faced a more liberal system under Thatcher than Sunak.

You might not know this, but both Ke Huy Quan and Hong Chau are Boat People. Their families fled Vietnam in 1978/79 following the end of the war, and they both came to the U.S. as refugees. Tonight, they're up for Best Actor/Best Supporting Actress at the Academy Awards 🥲💛 https://t.co/1rZxDzatpP
